(175, 1, '2015-11-20 13:27:25', '2015-11-20 07:57:25', '<b><a title=\"California State Route 75\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California_State_Route_75\">State Route 75</a></b> (SR75) is a 13-mile (21km) <a title=\"Limited-access road\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Limited-access_road\">expressway</a> in <a title=\"San Diego County, California\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Diego_County,_California\">San Diego County</a>, <a title=\"California\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California\">California</a>. It is a loop route of <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Interstate 5 (California)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interstate_5_(California)\">Interstate 5</a> that begins near<a title=\"Imperial Beach, California\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imperial_Beach,_California\">Imperial Beach</a>, heading west on Palm Avenue. The route continues north along the <a title=\"Silver Strand (San Diego)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Silver_Strand_(San_Diego)\">Silver Strand</a>, a thin strip of land bordering <a title=\"San Diego Bay\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Diego_Bay\">San Diego Bay</a>, through <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Silver Strand State Beach\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Silver_Strand_State_Beach\">Silver Strand State Beach</a>. SR 75 passes through the city of<a title=\"Coronado, California\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coronado,_California\">Coronado</a> as Orange Avenue <i>(pictured)</i> and continues onto the <a title=\"San DiegoCoronado Bridge\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Diego%E2%80%93Coronado_Bridge\">San DiegoCoronado Bay Bridge</a> over the bay, before joining back with Interstate 5 near downtown <a title=\"San Diego\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Diego\">San Diego</a> at a freeway interchange. Orange Avenue dates from the late 19th century, and the Silver Strand Highway was open to the public by 1924. What would become SR75 was added to 